  "course_description": "This course focuses on a specific body of literary texts, critical approach, or theoretical problem in the area of Comparative Literature. Students may repeat this course for credit if the subject matter varies.",
  "course_notes": "(Same as ENG 789 4, WGS 730 1, FREN 780 1, RLR 700, PHIL 789 2) The course will be based on readings of some of Derrida's earlier work (broadly speaking up to 1972), and attempt to come to as clear an understanding as possible of some basic Derridean terms and concepts (trace, writing, différance, deconstruction, iterability, metaphoricity, signature, quasi-transcendental...). We will also look in some detail at Derrida's polemical exchanges with Foucault, Lacan, and Searle.",
